{
  "texts": [
    "A DCZ gate includes two voltage pulses separated by an echoing two-tone X(π) pulse.",
    "The voltage pulse shape is designed to cancel any slow drift and compensation is applied to P1, P2 while exchange is being pulsed.",
    "We set a padding of 0.02 μs between two adjacent pulses.",
    "The real-time logic required for the FPGA to apply the sequences incur unintended gaps in the order of 0.1 μs between some of the quantum gates.",
    "This introduces both coherent and incoherent errors."
  ]
}